# The Overlap Newsletter - Design System & Context

## Project Overview
Newsletter at the intersection of music, marketing, and AI. 
**Story**: Built two 7-figure businesses (180K + 70K audiences), spoke at FunnelHackingLive, lost it all, now rebuilding from zero while learning AI.
**Tone**: Personal + vulnerable (but not performing), clearly authoritative, honest about struggle.
**Audience**: Musicians who care about business + Marketers obsessed with culture. Everyone needs to learn both.

## Brand Identity
**Name**: The Overlap
**Tagline**: "Where years of seven-figure marketing scale meets the reality of rebuilding with AI from ground zero"
**Core Values**: Real expertise, honest struggle, actual tactics

## Color Palette
- Primary Charcoal: #171e19
- Accent Yellow: #ffe17c
- Dark Gray: #272727
- Sage: #b7c6c2
- White: #ffffff
- Light Background: #f8f9fa

## Typography
- **Headlines**: Anton (uppercase, 8xl-9xl, line-height 0.9)
- **Body**: Satoshi (400/500/700 weights)
- Font Import: `https://api.fontshare.com/v2/css?f[]=anton@400&f[]=satoshi@400,500,700&display=swap`

## Design System Rules
- Grid background: 40px pattern with linear-gradient sage at 20% opacity
- Borders: 1px #171e19/10% on light, #b7c6c2/10% on dark
- Transitions: 300ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)
- Spacing: 4px base unit, consistent rhythm
- Radius scale: 2xl (16px), 3xl (24px), rounded-full

## Key Animation/Interactions
- Parallax geometric shapes moving on scroll (different speeds per layer)
- Cards hover with shadow increase + slight translate-y -2
- Featured issue: rotating borders on hover
- Yellow highlight bars with slight rotation animation
- Smooth color transitions on hover states

